               <p>JOHN HAWKINS. I am a <rs id="t18180218-77-viclabel404" type="occupation">broker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180218-77-victim500 t18180218-77-viclabel404"></join>; I live in <placeName id="t18180218-77-crimeloc405">Marylebone-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180218-77-crimeloc405" type="placeName" value="Marylebone-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180218-77-crimeloc405" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180218-77-off402 t18180218-77-crimeloc405"></join>. On the 12th of February, I lost my bedstead out of my passage.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM SAYERS. I am a watchman. I saw the prisoner with the bedstead on his back, at half-past nine o'clock at night. I stopped him; he said, he was going to take it home, to Bedford-street, and that he brought it from his lodgings - I took him to the watch-house.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A man gave it to me to carry.</p>
               <p>
